description: Borrowed from the Italian dialectal mustaccio (from Neapolitan) or mustacchio, ultimately from Ancient Greek.

entries.meaning: A mustache, especially a large or lush one.

verbs.description: mustachio (third-person singular simple present mustachios, present participle mustachioing, simple past and past participle mustachioed)

entries.meaning: To adorn with a mustachio, or something that resembles a mustachio.
